ication of the semantic differential technique. Psychological Bulletin <span id=\"bib.bib15.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">77</span>(5), 361–372 (1972)\n709\t\n710\t</span>\n711\t</li>\n712\t<li id=\"bib.bib16\" class=\"ltx_bibitem\">\n713\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_bibitem\">[16]</span>\n714\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\">\n715\tLiu, Y., et al.: Roberta: A robustly optimized bert pretraining approach. arXiv preprint arXiv:1907.11692 (2019)\n716\t\n717\t</span>\n718\t</li>\n719\t<li id=\"bib.bib17\" class=\"ltx_bibitem\">\n720\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_bibitem\">[17]</span>\n721\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\">\n722\tSmith, V.L., Clark, H.H.: On the course of answering questions. Journal of Memory and Language <span id=\"bib.bib17.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">32</span>(1), 25–38 (1993)\n723\t\n724\t</span>\n725\t</li>\n726\t<li id=\"bib.bib18\" class=\"ltx_bibitem\">\n727\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_bibitem\">[18]</span>\n728\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\">\n729\tSwerts, M., Krahmer, E.: Audiovisual prosody and feeling of knowing. Journal of Memory and Language <span id=\"bib.bib18.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">53</span>, 81–94 (2005)\n730\t\n731\t</span>\n732\t</li>\n733\t<li id=\"bib.bib19\" class=\"ltx_bibitem\">\n734\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_bibitem\">[19]</span>\n735\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\">\n736\tThompson, M.M., Zanna, M.P., Griffin, D.W.: Let’s not be indifferent about (attitudinal) ambivalence. In: Attitude Strength: Antecedents and Consequences. Lawrence Erlbaum (1995)\n737\t\n738\t</span>\n739\t</li>\n740\t<li id=\"bib.bib20\" class=\"ltx_bibitem\">\n741\t<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_bibitem\">[20]</span>\n742\t<span class=\"ltx_bibblock\">\n743\tVaswani, A., et al.: Attention is all you need. In: Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems (2017)\n744\t\n745\t</span>\n746\t</li>\n747\t</ul>\n748\t</section>\n749\t</article>\n750\t</div>\n751\t</div>\n752\t<footer class=\"arxiv-html-footer\">\n753\t  <d